summaries.short: After lacing up their corsets and powdering their wigs for a Victorian-themed ball, the houses deliver gender-bending group productions and historic hand performances that serve grandeur, opulence, and most of all, drama.
summaries.full: The houses lace up their corsets and powder their wigs for a Victorian-themed ball, where the royal court serves grandeur, opulence, and most of all, drama. After delivering a gender-bending group production that emphasizes a single element of vogue, each house entrusts one member to give a historic hand performance. Multi-platinum solo artist and Queen frontman Adam Lambert helps decide which team conquered the runway – and which faces the guillotine.

summaries.short: The first money ball of the season finds the houses embodying iconic toys as they compete across three categories – highlighting floor performance, European runway, and duck walk – worth a grand total of $30,000.
summaries.full: Motivated by the first money ball of the season, the competitors bring iconic toys to life in all-house productions highlighting dynamic floor performances – and a whole lotta leg – for a shot at $15,000. Next, duos and trios walk European runway in hopes of snagging $5,000 before a final team duck walk showdown worth $10,000. Which house will rake in enough cash to reign superior? Actress, socialite, and legendary face diva Amiyah Scott helps the judges decide.
